article.headline: Centenary 63, Houston 57
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Andrew Wisniewski scored 27 points, grabbed six rebounds and had seven steals, leading Centenary to a 63-57 win over Houston on Monday night. Rickey Evans added 15 points, and Chad Maclies had 11. Centenary trailed early, then closed to within 38-37 with 10:57 left in the second half. The Gents tied the score with 5:13 to play. Centenary's 17-of-20 free throw attempts helped put the game out of reach. Marcus Oliver led Houston (7-8) with 19 points. Andre Owens added 18 points. Houston opened the game with a 15-7 lead and was leading 30-24 at halftime.
